                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2001-08-05</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I was actually looking for a different book by him that had been recommended and purchased this on a whim.  It is excellent!  The stories are short, to the point, and often funny and/or extremely moving.  It inspires me to do more as a Christian.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Inspirational, often touching, sometimes challenging</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      /
                      <span>5</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2001-05-08</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This collection of human stories include ones personally experienced by Campolo and collected by him.  A very few were even familiar to me.  Most touched my heart in some way, such as the story of the street person who only wanted...but I'll let you read that yourself.  Campolo's book would be useful as a source for sermon or other teaching illustrations, though I fear it may be so popular as to reduce the effectiveness of it.  Hard to put down!</span>
                  
              
